RESUMO-CV.TEXTO-RESUMO-CV-RH-EN:
Americo Barbosa da Cunha Junior holds a bachelor's degree, a master's degree and a PhD in Mechanical Engineering from the Pontifical Catholic University of Rio de Janeiro (PUC-Rio), where he also graduated in Applied Mathematics. He also holds a second doctoral degree from the Université Paris-Est (UPE), the result of a Brazil-France cooperation agreement between PUC-Rio and UPE, which resulted in an 18-month internship in the Laboratoire Modélisation et Simulation Multi-Echelle in Paris . He is an Assistant Professor of Applied Mathematics at the Rio de Janeiro State University (UERJ) since April 2015. At UERJ he develops teaching, research and extension activities at the undergraduate and postgraduate levels, being an accredited lecturer at PPG-EM - Graduate Program in Mechanical Engineering (Engineering III) and CCOMP - Graduate Program in Sciences Computational (Multidisciplinary). He is the coordinator of NUMERICO - Nucleus of Modeling and Computational Experimentation of UERJ since its foundation in November of 2015. In July 2017 was elected, by the teaching pairs, Counselor of the Sub-rectory of Postgraduate and Research for a mandate of 24 months, and in January of 2018 assumed the Sub-head of the Department of Applied Mathematics, for a term of 2 years. In ABCM - Brazilian Association of Engineering and Mechanical Sciences participates as executive member of the Committee of Non-Linear and Chaotic Phenomena. He has participated, as coordinator or team member, in research and extension projects financed with public and private resources, from development agencies, foundations and companies. He is the author of more than 50 technical-scientific works and maintains collaboration with research groups in Brazil (UERJ, UFRJ, PUC-Rio, USP, UNESP, ITA and UTFPR) and abroad (UPE, Texas Tech, Nova de Lisboa, KAUST and Politechnika Lubelska). Due to these activities, in recent years, it has regularly participated in national and international scientific events, organized workshops and symposia, visited teaching and research institutions, and taught mini-courses in the area of &#8203;&#8203;Quantification of Uncertainties, both in Brazil and in Brazil. outside. He works in the areas of Mechanical Engineering and Applied and Computational Mathematics, with interest in the subjects Science and Computational Engineering; Quantification of Uncertainties; Nonlinear Dynamics; Inverse Problems; Industrial Mathematics.

